The GridSat-B1 infrared cloud product used as one of the two NOAA-stewarded
inputs to this work is provided and maintained by Kenneth R. Knapp (NOAA NCEI).
The microwave + infrared land surface emissivity inversion approach follows the
published work of Prigent, Rossow, Aires, and colleagues, with the TELSEM2
climatology of Aires et al. (2011) as the validation reference.

